@groundwater as I explained, I can't constantly reproduce. But I'll ship a version of my app with 1.4.15 and ask my (modest) user-base to report improvements (or not). For 1.5.0, since it's still in beta, I won't risk it but will give a try if no results with 1.4.15 .

> It appears the crashed tread is doing Geolocation: are you use that feature?

_apriori_ I'm not using that feature, but, as I explained, I'm loading different websites in `webviews` (like a web browser). So, it may one of those websites use geolocation. Is there a quick way to check this? Do you have something in mind I could try to track down?

Note also, that I'm doing something unusual on app-quit that can be a cause. Even if I've done that since long on my app and was not a problem apriori:

```js
// Delay app quiting to let some times for
// analytics to flush its queue
let askedToQuit = false;
app.on('will-quit', (e) => {
  if (!askedToQuit) {
    askedToQuit = true;
	
    // prevents ap to quit
    e.preventDefault();
	
    // flush at next tick to let some time to other trackings
    setImmediate(() =>
      analytics.flush(() => app.quit())
    );
  }
});
```

@kevinsawicki does the stack-trace you mapped give any more insights?
